## Pattern Examples: Organization Member Loading

There are two distinct systems for loading organization member data in this codebase: (1) **better-auth organization plugin** for auth-level org membership (Postgres), and (2) **ClickHouse user mappings** for analytics-level user identity. There is no existing pattern for getting a member count.

---

### Pattern 1: `authClient.organization.getFullOrganization` (Direct API Call with `useState`/`useEffect`)

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/OrganizationPage.tsx:22-65`
**Used for**: Loading full org details including members and invitations on the Organization management page.

```typescript
interface FullOrg {
	id: string;
	name: string;
	slug: string;
	members: readonly {
		id: string;
		userId: string;
		role: string;
		user: { id: string; name: string; email: string; image: string | null };
	}[];
	invitations: readonly {
		id: string;
		email: string;
		role: string | null;
		status: string;
	}[];
}

export function OrganizationPage() {
	const { activeOrg } = useOrganization();
	const [fullOrg, setFullOrg] = useState<FullOrg | null>(null);
	const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

	const fetchOrg = async () => {
		if (!activeOrg) return;
		setLoading(true);
		const res = await authClient.organization.getFullOrganization({
			query: { organizationId: activeOrg.id },
		});
		if (res.data) {
			setFullOrg(res.data as unknown as FullOrg);
		}
		setLoading(false);
	};

	// biome-ignore lint/correctness/useExhaustiveDependencies: refetch when org changes
	useEffect(() => {
		fetchOrg();
	}, [activeOrg?.id]);
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `authClient.organization.getFullOrganization` from `better-auth/client/plugins` (organizationClient)
- Manual `useState`/`useEffect` pattern (not TanStack Query)
- Response is cast with `as unknown as FullOrg` because the better-auth types do not match exactly
- `fetchOrg` is extracted as a standalone async function so it can be re-called after mutations (invite, remove, cancel)
- Returns both `members` and `invitations` arrays
- Members include nested `user` object with `id`, `name`, `email`, `image`

---

### Pattern 2: Members Rendered in the UI

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/OrganizationPage.tsx:201-252`
**Used for**: Displaying the member list with avatars, roles, and remove buttons.

```tsx
{loading ? (
	<p className="text-sm text-muted">Loading...</p>
) : (
	<div className="flex flex-col gap-2">
		{fullOrg?.members.map((m) => (
			<div
				key={m.id}
				className="flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg border border-border px-4 py-3"
			>
				<div className="flex items-center gap-3">
					{m.user.image ? (
						<img src={m.user.image} alt="" className="h-8 w-8 rounded-full" />
					) : (
						<div className="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-hover text-xs font-medium text-muted">
							{m.user.name.charAt(0).toUpperCase()}
						</div>
					)}
					<div>
						<p className="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">{m.user.name}</p>
						<p className="text-xs text-muted">{m.user.email}</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div className="flex items-center gap-2">
					<Badge variant={m.role === "owner" ? "default" : "secondary"}>
						{m.role}
					</Badge>
					{m.role !== "owner" && (
						<Button variant="outline" size="xs" onClick={() => handleRemoveMember(m.id)}>
							<Trash2 className="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
						</Button>
					)}
				</div>
			</div>
		))}
	</div>
)}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Iterates `fullOrg?.members` directly
- Owner members cannot be removed (role check)
- Avatar fallback uses first character of name
- Members array is accessed from the `FullOrg` state, not from a separate query

---

### Pattern 3: `OrganizationContext` (Active Org + Org List via better-auth hooks)

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/contexts/OrganizationContext.tsx:1-87`
**Used for**: Providing the active org and org list to the entire app. Does NOT include members.

```typescript
export function OrganizationProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
	const { data: activeOrg, isPending: activeLoading } =
		authClient.useActiveOrganization();
	const { data: orgs, isPending: listLoading } =
		authClient.useListOrganizations();
	const queryClient = useQueryClient();
	const [switching, setSwitching] = useState(false);

	// Auto-set active org if none is set but user has orgs
	useEffect(() => {
		if (
			!activeLoading &&
			!listLoading &&
			!activeOrg &&
			orgs &&
			orgs.length > 0 &&
			!switching
		) {
			setSwitching(true);
			authClient.organization
				.setActive({ organizationId: orgs[0].id })
				.then(() => queryClient.invalidateQueries())
				.finally(() => setSwitching(false));
		}
	}, [activeOrg, orgs, activeLoading, listLoading, switching, queryClient]);

	const switchOrg = async (orgId: string) => {
		setSwitching(true);
		try {
			await authClient.organization.setActive({ organizationId: orgId });
			await queryClient.invalidateQueries();
		} finally {
			setSwitching(false);
		}
	};

	return (
		<OrganizationContext.Provider
			value={{
				activeOrg: activeOrg ?? null,
				organizations: orgs ?? [],
				switchOrg,
				isLoading: activeLoading || listLoading || switching,
			}}
		>
			{children}
		</OrganizationContext.Provider>
	);
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `authClient.useActiveOrganization()` and `authClient.useListOrganizations()` -- built-in better-auth React hooks
- The `Organization` interface has `id`, `name`, `slug`, `logo` -- no `members` field
- Auto-sets the first org as active if none is active
- Consumed everywhere via `useOrganization()` hook
- This context does NOT load members; it only tracks which org is active and the list of orgs

---

### Pattern 4: `userMappings` via oRPC/TanStack Query (ClickHouse analytics users)

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/DevelopersListPage.tsx:40-54` (and 6 other pages)
**Used for**: Mapping ClickHouse `user_id` values to human-readable usernames (extracted from project paths).

```typescript
const { data: userMappings } = useQuery(
	orpc.analytics.users.mappings.queryOptions({ input: { days: 30 } }),
);

const userMap = useMemo(() => {
	const map = new Map<string, string>();
	if (userMappings) {
		for (const m of userMappings) {
			map.set(m.user_id, m.username);
		}
	}
	return map;
}, [userMappings]);

const userMapRecord = useMemo(() => Object.fromEntries(userMap), [userMap]);
```

**Key aspects**:
- This is a **different concept** from org members -- these are ClickHouse analytics users, not better-auth organization members
- Uses TanStack Query via `orpc.analytics.users.mappings.queryOptions()`
- The same pattern is repeated in 7 pages: `DevelopersListPage`, `SessionsListPage`, `DeveloperDetailPage`, `ROIPage`, `LearningsPage`, `ErrorsPage`, `ProjectDetailPage`
- Creates both a `Map<string, string>` and a `Record<string, string>` depending on consumer needs
- Server-side implementation at `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/api/src/services/user.service.ts:24-82` extracts usernames from project paths (e.g., `/Users/marc/...` becomes `marc`)

---

### Pattern 5: Organization Mutation + Refetch

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/pages/dashboard/OrganizationPage.tsx:67-99`
**Used for**: Inviting members, removing members, cancelling invitations -- all followed by refetching the full org.

```typescript
const handleInvite = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
	e.preventDefault();
	if (!inviteEmail.trim()) return;
	setInviting(true);
	const res = await authClient.organization.inviteMember({
		email: inviteEmail.trim(),
		role: inviteRole as "member" | "admin",
	});
	if (res.data) {
		const link = `${window.location.origin}/invitation/${res.data.id}`;
		setInviteLink(link);
		setInviteEmail("");
		await fetchOrg(); // refetch members
	}
	setInviting(false);
};

const handleRemoveMember = async (memberIdOrEmail: string) => {
	await authClient.organization.removeMember({ memberIdOrEmail });
	await fetchOrg(); // refetch members
};

const handleCancelInvitation = async (invitationId: string) => {
	await authClient.organization.cancelInvitation({ invitationId });
	await fetchOrg(); // refetch members
};
```

**Key aspects**:
- All mutations call `fetchOrg()` afterwards to refresh the member/invitation lists
- `authClient.organization.inviteMember`, `removeMember`, `cancelInvitation` are the mutation methods available
- No TanStack Query mutation -- plain async calls with manual state management

---

### Pattern 6: Accept Invitation Flow

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/pages/AcceptInvitationPage.tsx:28-51`
**Used for**: Accepting an org invitation and switching to that org.

```typescript
const handleAccept = async () => {
	if (!invitationId) return;
	setStatus("accepting");
	setError(null);

	const res = await authClient.organization.acceptInvitation({
		invitationId,
	});

	if (res.error) {
		setError(res.error.message ?? "Failed to accept invitation");
		setStatus("error");
		return;
	}

	if (res.data) {
		await authClient.organization.setActive({
			organizationId: res.data.member.organizationId,
		});
	}

	setStatus("accepted");
	setTimeout(() => navigate("/dashboard"), 1500);
};
```

---

### Existing Member Count Pattern

There is **no existing pattern** for getting a member count in the codebase. The only place where members are loaded is `OrganizationPage.tsx` via `getFullOrganization`, which returns the full `members` array. If you needed a count, you would derive it from `fullOrg.members.length`.

---

### Summary of All `authClient.organization` Methods Used

| Method | File | Line |
|--------|------|------|
| `getFullOrganization` | `OrganizationPage.tsx` | 53 |
| `inviteMember` | `OrganizationPage.tsx` | 71 |
| `removeMember` | `OrganizationPage.tsx` | 92 |
| `cancelInvitation` | `OrganizationPage.tsx` | 97 |
| `acceptInvitation` | `AcceptInvitationPage.tsx` | 33 |
| `rejectInvitation` | `AcceptInvitationPage.tsx` | 55 |
| `setActive` | `OrganizationContext.tsx` | 49, 58 / `AcceptInvitationPage.tsx` | 44 |
| `useActiveOrganization` | `OrganizationContext.tsx` | 31 |
| `useListOrganizations` | `OrganizationContext.tsx` | 33 |

### Auth Client Setup

**Found in**: `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/milan/apps/web/src/lib/auth-client.ts:1-15`

```typescript
import { organizationClient } from "better-auth/client/plugins";
import { createAuthClient } from "better-auth/react";
import { queryClient } from "./query-client";

export const authClient = createAuthClient({
	baseURL: "",
	plugins: [organizationClient()],
});
```

The `organizationClient()` plugin from `better-auth` provides all the `authClient.organization.*` methods and hooks.

